  "prompt": "Is there a 5 star general?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the rank of \"five-star general,\" also known as \"General of the Army\" in the United States, is not currently active and has not been awarded since World War II. This rank was created during World War II and was held by only a few individuals: George C. Marshall, Douglas MacArthur, Dwight D. Eisenhower, Henry H. Arnold (who was General of the Army and later General of the Air Force), and Omar N. Bradley.\n\nThe five-star rank was primarily established to ensure that U.S. military officers would not be outranked by their counterparts in other nations' armed forces during World War II. Since then, no one else has been promoted to this rank, and it is generally reserved for wartime conditions when a significant senior command role is necessary.",
